Package: ManyIVsNets
Type: Package
Title: Environmental Phillips Curve Analysis with Multiple Instrumental
        Variables and Networks
Version: 0.1.1
Date: 2025-06-07
Authors@R: person("Avishek", "Bhandari", 
                  email = "bavisek@gmail.com", 
                  role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
Description: Comprehensive toolkit for Environmental Phillips Curve (EPC) analysis 
    featuring multidimensional instrumental variable creation, transfer entropy 
    causal discovery, network analysis, and state-of-the-art econometric methods.
    Implements geographic, technological, migration, geopolitical, financial, 
    and natural risk instruments with robust diagnostics and visualization.
    Provides 24 different instrumental variable approaches with empirical validation.
    Methods based on Phillips (1958) <doi:10.1111/j.1468-0335.1958.tb00003.x>,
    Schreiber (2000) <doi:10.1103/PhysRevLett.85.461>, and 
    Stock & Yogo (2005) <doi:10.1017/CBO9780511614491.006>.
